:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Cl</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">aimant’s lawyers are also frequen</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">tly faced with the need to make the assessment of pro</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">pects of success </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">based on</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> only limited </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">information.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The process has been described as being one:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">          “which falls to be conducted with all the cards face upwards on the table  and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">[where] </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">the vast majority of the cards will start in the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">[public] </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">authority’s hands.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">”</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Claimant</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">him or herself </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">often does not have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">access to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> formal policy </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">documents</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> or even a written explanat</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ion of a decision.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="22" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">As the pre-action p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rotocol makes clear</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, the protocol itself</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">does not create any pre-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">action obligation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to make disc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">los</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ure of releva</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nt  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">information</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="23" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Claimant</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> can</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> where applicable</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> make use of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rights  conferred by</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the Data Protection Act </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1998 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and the Freedom of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Information</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Act </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2005 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">but</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the former only requires a “</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">prompt” </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> response which must be made within </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">40 days (nearly 7 week</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s) and the latter </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">has an equivalent time requirement which uses </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">20 days (3 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">eeks) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">as a backstop. Furthermore, under</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Freedom</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Information</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Act</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">time is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> suspended fro</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">m </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the date of notification</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> of any fee </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> be paid until</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> payment.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In any event</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, public</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> authorities often do</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> no</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t comply with the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">time </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">requirements and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, although complaint can be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">made to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Information</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Commissioner</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Commissioner’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> workload is such </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">that this</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> can take m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">any months to process. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-a